Package ConcreteDomain.AtomicTypes

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AbsoluteTimePoint
    This class is a wrapper for LocalDateTime.
    BooleanObject
    This is just a wrapper for a Boolean value.
    BooleanType
    The instances of this class are Boolean types with different applications.
    ConstantObject
    This class is just a wrapper for strings.
    Duration
    The class models temporal extensions in the Gregorian Calendar.
    Example: 3 months, 55.7 minutes
    EnumerationObject
    This class is a wrapper for a concrete object of the EnumerationType Example: for the colors: red,green,blue, it might represent green
    EnumerationType
    This class models finite lists of Strings as enumeration type.
    ExtensionConcept
    This class models extensions like "3 semesters" or "5 working days".
    ExtensionLength
    This class represents extensions like 3 kilometers or 5 millimeters
    ExtensionUnit
    This is the abstract superclass for those extension types consisting of a value a unit of measurement.
    FloatObject
    This is a wrapper class for float values.
    IntegerObject
    This is just a wrapper for int values.
    NumberObject
    This is the abstract superclass of all number objects (Integer, Float, Double).
    PhysicalHost
    This class enables using the access data (hostname and port) about physical hosts as attribute values.
    RelativeTimePoint
    This class represents relative time points like 10:15 or 10:15:6 (hour minute second)
    week 3 10:15 (every third day in a week, hour minute second)
    month 3 10:15 (every third month in a week, hour minute second)
    3 w 10:15 (every third week in a year, hour minute second)
    2 m 10:15 (every third month in a yead, hour minute second)
    3 m 2 d 10:15 (every third month, every second day in this month, hour minute second)
    and similar.
    StringObject
    This is a wrapper for strings.
